OOC: I have a day off today, so I&#39;m getting myself caught up.  Expect a
string of emails.

Lord Perseus: Deluxe
Salveo, Guardia, Ravenchief: Basic
Trelos: Mega
Celeron: between Basic and Deluxe

On Tue, Aug 9, 2011 at 5:02 PM, Super Cyclonus &lt;supercyclonus@...&gt;wrote:

&gt; In an effort to streamline a bit and to bring us more in line with the
&gt; predominantly Beast Wars style of the game that is a question I am
&gt; putting out there.
&gt;
&gt; WHAT SIZE IS YOUR CCHARACTER
&gt;
&gt; Beast Wars pretty much had the sizes: Basic, Deluxe, Mega, Ultra
&gt;
&gt; For the characters that are part of the Beast Wars line we already can
&gt; get the sizes, but for those who have made up characters or who have
&gt; imported them from other realms, how big are they?
&gt;
&gt; Yeah I know that sizes tended to fluxuate somewhat, but I am looking
&gt; to get somewhat standard if I can.
&gt;
&gt; To help I have put a list in the files section listing the sizes of
&gt; different ones. I know it may not list EVERY character, but it hits
&gt; most. And generally a mega is bigger than a Deluxe and a Deluxe bigger
&gt; than a basic although there may be some exceptions. I do believe Rat
&gt; Trap made it to Deluxe as a TM, but never got any taller.
&gt;
&gt; I can start:
&gt;
&gt; Rodimus Prime, being a Prime should be the same size as Optimus which
&gt; would make him an Ultra.
&gt;
&gt; Cyclonus I would make the same size, since at times he was drawn as
&gt; big or even bigger than Galvatron and comparable to Ultra Magnus. So
&gt; he would be leader sized.
&gt;
&gt; Scourge is somewhat smaller and would be a Mega
&gt; Deepstryke would be a mega
&gt; Phobia and Black Razor would be Deluxes.
&gt; Lord Elder, as he is based on K9 would be a Deluxe.
&gt;
&gt; As suggestions:
&gt;
&gt; Tuscon = Ultra
&gt; Hydras = Ultra
&gt; Nightshift = Mega or more likely Deluxe
&gt; Straight Shot = Basic
&gt; Quickstride = Deluxe
&gt;
&gt; What are your thoughts?
&gt;
&gt; - Preston
